## Franchise conditions

You may operate a Dumper's Repo franchise instance only if you comply with
ALL of the following:

1. **Branding** — The primary application header must continue to identify the
   product as "Dumper's Repo" (including the Buy. Craft. Sell. slogan or
   equivalent brand treatment required by the reference deployment).

2. **No monetization** — You must not charge any fee for access to the
   Software, for hosting the franchise, or for using Dumper's Repo features.
   Membership approval and org privacy rules are allowed; paywalls for app
   access are not.

3. **Dumpers Fair-Value Pricing (DFP)** — DFP is a proprietary formula and
   trade secret of Michael Linzenmeyer. You must use the official DFP engine
   loaded from the canonical URL published by the licensor (currently
   https://www.dumpers-repo.com/dfp-engine.js and dfp-version.json). You
   may not tamper with, reverse-engineer for reuse, replace, circumvent, or
   self-host an alternate DFP engine in production.

   **Display opt-out (permitted):** A super-admin may disable DFP display for
   their instance. If DFP values are hidden from the UI, every page must
   display this notice in the site footer:

   "This franchise has opted out of using/displaying Dumpers Fair-Value
   Pricing (DFP)."

   Hiding DFP without this notice is a license violation.

4. **Distribution** — You must include unmodified copies of this LICENSE and
   TRADEMARK.md with any fork or deployment, and identify the deployment as a
   Dumper's Repo franchise instance (not the official dumpers-repo.com unless
   authorized).

## Prohibited conduct

- Removing or replacing Dumper's Repo as the product identity
- Implying official endorsement by dumpers-repo.com without permission
- Charging fees for access or franchise hosting
- Tampering with, modifying, or circumventing DFP
- Using Dumper's Repo brand marks on unrelated software

## Termination

Any violation of these franchise conditions terminates your license to use
and deploy the Software immediately. Upon termination you must cease deployment
and destroy proprietary DFP materials in your possession except as required
by law.

